Yes. this'll do nicely.

513
00:47:05.205 --> 00:47:08.538
You don't remember me. do you?
Why should you?

514
00:47:08.642 --> 00:47:10.974
I was just a little nip
that you hired for a couple of weeks.

515
00:47:11.078 --> 00:47:13.046
sweeping up hair.

516
00:47:13.981 --> 00:47:16.040
But I remember these.

517
00:47:16.883 --> 00:47:19.909
And how could
I ever forget you. Mr. Barker.

518
00:47:24.224 --> 00:47:26.385
I used to sit right here.

519
00:47:27.327 --> 00:47:30.194
Dream of the day
when I could be a proper barber myself.

520
00:47:30.297 --> 00:47:34.028
You might say that you was
inspiration to me.

521
00:47:46.380 --> 00:47:48.245
So. is we got a deal?

522
00:47:49.650 --> 00:47:53.677
Or should I run down the street
to me old pal. Beadle Bamford?

523
00:47:57.290 --> 00:48:01.488
What do you say to that. now.
Mr. Sweeney Todd?

524
00:48:24.151 --> 00:48:27.177
My. my. my. Always work to be done.

525
00:48:27.287 --> 00:48:29.619
Spic and span. that's my motto.

526
00:48:42.302 --> 00:48:45.669
So. how'd you end up
with that dreadful Italian?

527
00:48:45.772 --> 00:48:50.141
Got me from the workhouse.
Been there since I was born.

528
00:48:50.243 --> 00:48:52.837
Oh. God!
He's got an appointment with his tailor!

529
00:48:52.946 --> 00:48:54.538
If he's late. he'll blame me!

530
00:48:54.648 --> 00:48:55.910
Wait!

531
00:49:02.556 --> 00:49:05.081
Signor! You got an appointment!

532
00:49:10.330 --> 00:49:14.130
Signor Pirelli's been called away.
Better run after him.

533
00:49:15.102 --> 00:49:19.539
No. sir. I should stay here.
or it'll be a lashing.

534
00:49:19.639 --> 00:49:22.335
He's a great one for the lashings.

535
00:49:28.215 --> 00:49:29.375
So.

536
00:49:30.684 --> 00:49:34.620
-Mrs. Lovett gave you a pie. did she?
-She's a real lady.

537
00:49:35.489 --> 00:49:37.116
That she is.

538
00:49:41.995 --> 00:49:46.989
But if I know a growing boy.
there's still room for more pie. eh?

539
00:49:47.100 --> 00:49:48.397
Yes. sir.

540
00:49:49.669 --> 00:49:52.467
Then why don't you wait
for your master downstairs?

541
00:49:52.572 --> 00:49:56.941
-Be another pie in it for you. I'm sure.
-No. I should stay here.

542
00:49:59.679 --> 00:50:03.615
Tell you what.
why don't you tell Mrs. Lovett

543
00:50:03.717 --> 00:50:07.175
that I said to give you
a nice big tot of gin.

544
00:50:07.287 --> 00:50:08.845
Thank you. sir!

545
00:51:16.857 --> 00:51:19.155
This is the second time. sir.

546
00:51:19.259 --> 00:51:22.387
you have been brought
before this bench.

547
00:51:23.630 --> 00:51:27.726
Though it is my earnest wish ever
to temper justice with mercy.

548
00:51:27.834 --> 00:51:30.997
your persistent dedication
to a life of crime

549
00:51:31.104 --> 00:51:34.767
is an abomination before God and man.

550
00:51:34.875 --> 00:51:38.333
I therefore sentence you
to hang by the neck until you're dead.

551
00:51:38.445 --> 00:51:41.414
And may the Lord
have mercy on your soul.

552
00:51:42.482 --> 00:51:44.245
Court is adjourned.

553
00:51:53.226 --> 00:51:55.717
Thank you. Your Honor.

554
00:51:55.829 --> 00:51:59.265
-Just the sentence we wanted.
-Was he guilty?

555
00:51:59.366 --> 00:52:00.492
Well. if he didn't do it.

556
00:52:00.600 --> 00:52:03.034
he's surely done
something to warrant a hanging.

557
00:52:03.136 --> 00:52:05.832
-What man has not?
-Sorry?

558
00:52:08.842 --> 00:52:10.605
No matter. Come.

559
00:52:11.811 --> 00:52:13.472
Walk home with me.

560
00:52:16.516 --> 00:52:19.212
I have news for you. my friend.

561
00:52:19.319 --> 00:52:22.345
In order to shield her
from the evils of this world.

562
00:52:22.455 --> 00:52:25.788
I have decided to marry
my dear Johanna.

563
00:52:25.892 --> 00:52:28.292
Sir. happy news indeed.

564
00:52:28.395 --> 00:52:29.953
Strange though.

565
00:52:30.563 --> 00:52:36.229
when I offered myself to her.
she showed a certain reluctance.

566
00:52:37.137 --> 00:52:39.833
Excuse me. my lord
May I request. my lord

567
00:52:39.940 --> 00:52:42.340
Permission. my lord. to speak?

568
00:52:42.442 --> 00:52:44.706
Forgive me if I suggest. my lord

569
00:52:44.811 --> 00:52:47.177
You're looking less
than your best. my lord

570
00:52:47.280 --> 00:52:51.979
There's powder upon your vest. my lord
And stubble upon your cheek

571
00:52:55.121 --> 00:52:59.023
And ladies. my lord. are weak

572
00:52:59.826 --> 00:53:02.090
Stubble. you say?

573
00:53:05.432 --> 00:53:08.890
Perhaps I am
a little overhasty in the mornings.

574
00:53:10.003 --> 00:53:12.471
Fret not though. my lord
I know a place. my lord

575
00:53:12.572 --> 00:53:15.097
A barber. my lord. of skill

576
00:53:15.208 --> 00:53:17.403
Thus armed with a shaven face. my lord

577
00:53:17.510 --> 00:53:19.808
Some eau de cologne to grace. my lord

578
00:53:19.913 --> 00:53:22.381
And musk to enhance the chase
my lord

579
00:53:22.482 --> 00:53:25.349
You'll dazzle the girl until

580
00:53:26.252 --> 00:53:27.617
Until?

581
00:53:28.188 --> 00:53:32.386
She bows to your every will

582
00:53:33.460 --> 00:53:34.757
Barber?

583
00:53:36.062 --> 00:53:37.086
Take me to him.

584
00:53:37.197 --> 00:53:41.896
His name is Todd. my lord. and he is
the very last word in barbering.

585
00:53:48.575 --> 00:53:52.011
You ought to slow down a bit. lad.
It'll go straight to your head.

586
00:53:52.112 --> 00:53:53.704
They used to give it to us
in the workhouse

587
00:53:53.813 --> 00:53:55.576
so as we could sleep.

588
00:53:55.682 --> 00:53:57.843
Not that you'd want
to sleep in that place. ma'am.

589
00:53:57.951 --> 00:54:00.317
Not with the things
what happen in the dark.

590
00:54:00.420 --> 00:54:01.751
That's nice. dear.

591
00:54:01.855 --> 00:54:03.686
Think I'll just pop in
on Mr. Todd for a tick.

592
00:54:03.790 --> 00:54:06.623
-You all right. there?
-Leave the bottle.

593
00:54:11.631 --> 00:54:15.032
That lad is drinking me
out of house and home.

594
00:54:16.036 --> 00:54:18.368
How long till Pirelli gets back?

595
00:54:19.005 --> 00:54:20.734
He won't be back.

596
00:54:22.609 --> 00:54:24.474
Mr. T. you didn't.

597
00:54:35.688 --> 00:54:39.283
You're barking mad.
Killing a man what done you no harm.

598
00:54:40.126 --> 00:54:44.062
He recognized me from the old days.
Tried to blackmail me.

599
00:54:45.331 --> 00:54:46.958
Half me earnings.

600
00:54:47.667 --> 00:54:50.465
Oh. well. it's a different matter then.

601
00:54:51.371 --> 00:54:54.863
For a moment there.
I thought you'd lost your marbles.

602
00:54:57.944 --> 00:54:59.571
All that blood.

603
00:55:01.081 --> 00:55:02.548
Poor bugger.

604
00:55:03.416 --> 00:55:04.781
Oh. well.

605
00:55:13.193 --> 00:55:15.593
Well. waste not. want not.

606
00:55:17.230 --> 00:55:20.495
So. what are we gonna do
about the boy then?

607
00:55:22.001 --> 00:55:23.525
Send him up.

608
00:55:24.471 --> 00:55:27.440
Oh. we don't need to worry about him.
He's a simple thing.

609
00:55:27.540 --> 00:55:29.064
Send him up!

610
00:55:31.978 --> 00:55:35.436
Now. Mr. T.
surely one's enough for today.

611
00:55:36.583 --> 00:55:40.075
Besides. I was thinking of hiring the lad
to help me run the shop.

612
00:55:40.186 --> 00:55:43.155
Your poor knees
aren't what they used to be.

613
00:55:43.957 --> 00:55:45.390
All right.

614
00:55:47.427 --> 00:55:49.725
Course. we're gonna
have to stock up on the gin.

615
00:55:49.829 --> 00:55:51.854
Boy drinks like a sailor.

616
00:55:56.002 --> 00:55:57.299
The Judge.

617
00:56:00.807 --> 00:56:02.069
Get out.

618
00:56:04.144 --> 00:56:05.406
Get out!

619
00:56:21.794 --> 00:56:23.284
Mr. Todd?

620
00:56:24.330 --> 00:56:25.957
At your service.

621
00:56:27.133 --> 00:56:30.261
An honor to receive
your patronage. my lord.

622
00:56:31.538 --> 00:56:33.233
You know me. sir?

623
00:56:33.640 --> 00:56:38.873
Who in this wide world
does not know the great Judge Turpin?

624
00:56:45.485 --> 00:56:47.385
These premises
are hardly prepossessing.

625
00:56:47.487 --> 00:56:49.318
and yet the Beadle tells me

626
00:56:49.422 --> 00:56:53.324
you're the most accomplished
of all the barbers in the city.

627
00:56:53.993 --> 00:56:56.359
That is gracious of him. sir.

628
00:56:57.430 --> 00:56:59.864
What may I do for you today. sir?

629
00:57:00.633 --> 00:57:03.431
A stylish trimming of the hair?

630
00:57:03.536 --> 00:57:05.527
Soothing skin massage?

631
00:57:05.638 --> 00:57:07.367
Sit. sir. Sit.

632
00:57:08.541 --> 00:57:13.501
You see. sir. a man infatuate with love
Her ardent and eager slave

633
00:57:13.613 --> 00:57:18.516
So fetch the pomade and pumice stone
And lend me a more seductive tone

634
00:57:18.618 --> 00:57:23.055
A sprinkling perhaps of French cologne
But first. sir. I think

635
00:57:24.123 --> 00:57:26.717
a shave

636
00:57:28.494 --> 00:57:31.588
The closest I ever gave

637
00:57:36.236 --> 00:57:38.534
You're in a merry mood today. Mr. Todd.

638
00:57:38.638 --> 00:57:43.803
'Tis your delight. sir. catching fire
From one man to the next

639
00:57:43.910 --> 00:57:46.470
'Tis true. sir. love can still inspire

640
00:57:46.579 --> 00:57:48.979
The blood to pound
the heart leap higher

641
00:57:49.082 --> 00:57:50.447
- What more
- What more

642
00:57:50.550 --> 00:57:52.711
-can man require than love. sir
-can man require

643
00:57:52.819 --> 00:57:54.013
More than love. sir

644
00:57:54.120 --> 00:57:55.417
- What. sir?
- Women

645
00:57:55.521 --> 00:57:57.955
-Yes. women
-Pretty women

646
00:58:29.155 --> 00:58:33.319
Now then. my friend

647
00:58:34.427 --> 00:58:38.295
Now to your purpose

648
00:58:39.299 --> 00:58:43.030
Patience. enjoy it

649
00:58:43.903 --> 00:58:48.340
Revenge can't be taken in haste

650
00:58:48.441 --> 00:58:50.636
Make haste. and if we wed
You'll be commended. sir

651
00:58:50.743 --> 00:58:52.108
My lord

652
00:58:54.714 --> 00:58:57.148
And who. may it be said
Is your intended. sir?

653
00:58:57.250 --> 00:58:59.741
My ward

654
00:59:00.987 --> 00:59:03.319
A pretty little rosebud.

655
00:59:03.423 --> 00:59:05.323
Pretty as her mother?

656
00:59:06.359 --> 00:59:08.953
What? What was that?

657
00:59:09.062 --> 00:59:13.362
Nothing. sir. Nothing. May we proceed?

658
00:59:15.101 --> 00:59:16.693
Pretty women

659
00:59:17.303 --> 00:59:21.672
Fascinating
Sipping coffee

660
00:59:22.542 --> 00:59:27.673
Dancing
Pretty women!

661
00:59:27.780 --> 00:59:30.146
Are a wonder

662
00:59:30.249 --> 00:59:32.717
Pretty women

663
00:59:35.521 --> 00:59:40.390
Sitting in the window or

664
00:59:40.493 --> 00:59:45.396
Standing on the stair

665
00:59:45.498 --> 00:59:52.097
Something in them
Cheers the air

666
00:59:55.775 --> 00:59:57.572
Pretty women

667
00:59:58.578 --> 01:00:00.409
Silhouetted

668
01:00:01.047 --> 01:00:03.447
Stay within you

669
01:00:03.549 --> 01:00:06.074
Glancing!

670
01:00:06.185 --> 01:00:08.449
Stay forever

671
01:00:08.554 --> 01:00:11.182
Breathing lightly

672
01:00:11.290 --> 01:00:13.383
Pretty women

673
01:00:13.493 --> 01:00:15.893
-Pretty women
-Pretty women

674
01:00:15.995 --> 01:00:20.762
-Blowing out their candles or
-Blowing out their candles or

675
01:00:20.867 --> 01:00:24.132
-Combing out their hair
-Combing out their hair

676
01:00:24.237 --> 01:00:25.761
Then they leave

677
01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:27.772
-Even when they leave...
-Even when they

678
01:00:27.874 --> 01:00:29.398
leave you and vanish...

679
01:00:29.509 --> 01:00:32.410
-... they still...
-... they somehow can still remain...

680
01:00:32.512 --> 01:00:37.973
-...are there. they're there
-... there with you

681
01:00:38.084 --> 01:00:39.108
-Pretty women
-Pretty women

682
01:00:39.218 --> 01:00:40.742
-At their mirrors
-In their gardens

683
01:00:40.853 --> 01:00:42.377
-Letter-writing
-Flower-picking

684
01:00:42.488 --> 01:00:43.512
weather-watching

685
01:00:43.623 --> 01:00:48.424
-How they make a man sing
-How they make a man sing

686
01:00:48.528 --> 01:00:51.053
-Proof of heaven
-Proof of heaven

687
01:00:51.164 --> 01:00:53.496
-As you're living
-As you're living

688
01:00:53.599 --> 01:00:55.999
-Pretty women. sir!
-Pretty women. sir!

689
01:00:56.102 --> 01:00:58.195
-Pretty women. yes!
-Pretty women. yes!

690
01:00:58.304 --> 01:01:01.705
-Pretty women. sir
-Pretty women. pretty women

691
01:01:01.808 --> 01:01:03.400
Mr. Todd! I've seen Johanna

692
01:01:03.509 --> 01:01:06.239
and she said
she'd leave with me tonight.

693
01:01:08.514 --> 01:01:09.913
You.

694
01:01:10.016 --> 01:01:14.214
There is indeed a higher power
to warn me thus in time.

695
01:01:14.320 --> 01:01:16.220
Johanna elope with you?

696
01:01:17.990 --> 01:01:19.116
I'll make sure that neither you

697
01:01:19.225 --> 01:01:22.524
nor any other man
shall ever set eyes on her again.

698
01:01:23.229 --> 01:01:24.696
As for you. barber.

699
01:01:24.797 --> 01:01:27.231
it's all too clear
what company you keep.

700
01:01:27.333 --> 01:01:29.426
Service them well
and hold their custom.

701
01:01:29.535 --> 01:01:31.332
for you'll have none of mine.

702
01:01:31.437 --> 01:01:33.667
-Mr. Todd. You have to help me.
-Out.

703
01:01:33.773 --> 01:01:35.172
-Mr. Todd. please.
-Out.

704
01:01:35.274 --> 01:01:37.208
-Mr. Todd!
-Out!

705
01:01:42.882 --> 01:01:44.179
All this shouting and running about.

706
01:01:44.283 --> 01:01:46.444
-What's happened?
-I had him.

707
01:01:46.552 --> 01:01:47.746
The sailor busted in. I know.

708
01:01:47.854 --> 01:01:49.287
And then I saw them both
running down the stairs.

709
01:01:49.388 --> 01:01:50.855
I had him!

710
01:01:50.957 --> 01:01:53.016
His throat was bare beneath my hand

711
01:01:53.125 --> 01:01:56.026
-There. there. dear. Calm down.
-No. I had him!

712
01:01:56.128 --> 01:01:58.562
His throat was there
And he'll never come again!

713
01:01:58.664 --> 01:02:01.599
Easy now. Hush. love. hush

714
01:02:01.701 --> 01:02:03.726
-I'll keep telling you
- When?

715
01:02:03.836 --> 01:02:05.929
-What's your rush?
-Why did I wait?

716
01:02:06.038 --> 01:02:09.940
You told me to wait!
Now he'll never come again!

717
01:02:12.478 --> 01:02:14.378
There's a hole in the world
like a great black pit

718
01:02:14.480 --> 01:02:16.380
And it's filled with people
who are filled with shit

719
01:02:16.482 --> 01:02:19.645
And the vermin of the world inhabit it

720
01:02:19.752 --> 01:02:22.277
But not for long!

721
01:02:25.391 --> 01:02:29.623
They all deserve to die

722
01:02:29.729 --> 01:02:34.132
Tell you why. Mrs. Lovett
Tell you why

723
01:02:34.233 --> 01:02:36.997
Because in all of
the whole human race. Mrs. Lovett

724
01:02:37.103 --> 01:02:39.435
There are two kinds of men
and only two

725
01:02:39.539 --> 01:02:41.632
There's the one staying put
In his proper place

726
01:02:41.741 --> 01:02:44.039
And the one with his foot
In the other one's face

727
01:02:44.143 --> 01:02:46.304
Look at me. Mrs. Lovett. look at you!

728
01:02:46.412 --> 01:02:50.746
No. we all deserve to die

729
01:02:50.850 --> 01:02:55.287
Even you. Mrs. Lovett
Even I

730
01:02:55.388 --> 01:02:58.118
Because the lives of the wicked
should be made brief

731
01:02:58.224 --> 01:03:00.419
For the rest of us. death will be a relief

732
01:03:00.526 --> 01:03:04.826
We all deserve to die

733
01:03:04.931 --> 01:03:11.063
And I'll never see Johanna

734
01:03:11.170 --> 01:03:17.302
No. I'll never hug my girl to me

735
01:03:17.410 --> 01:03:19.139
Finished!

736
01:03:20.513 --> 01:03:24.210
All right! You. sir. How about a shave?

737
01:03:24.317 --> 01:03:28.083
Come and visit
your good friend Sweeney.

738
01:03:28.187 --> 01:03:31.020
You. sir. too. sir.
Welcome to the grave!

739
01:03:31.123 --> 01:03:35.116
I will have vengeance

740
01:03:35.227 --> 01:03:40.358
I will have salvation

741
01:03:42.301 --> 01:03:43.290
Who. sir?

742
01:03:43.402 --> 01:03:46.064
You. sir? No one's in the chair.
Come on. come on.

743
01:03:46.172 --> 01:03:49.733
Sweeney's waiting! I want you bleeders.

744
01:03:49.842 --> 01:03:53.141
You. sir! Anybody!
Gentlemen. now don't be shy!

745
01:03:53.245 --> 01:03:58.911
Not one man. no. nor ten men

746
01:03:59.018 --> 01:04:05.446
Nor a hundred can assuage me

747
01:04:05.558 --> 01:04:09.460
I will have you

748
01:04:10.029 --> 01:04:13.556
And I will get him back
Even as he gloats

749
01:04:13.666 --> 01:04:16.965
In the meantime
I'll practice on less honorable throats

750
01:04:17.069 --> 01:04:23.338
And my Lucy lies in ashes

751
01:04:23.442 --> 01:04:30.075
And I'll never see my girl again

752
01:04:30.182 --> 01:04:33.674
But the work waits!

753
01:04:34.887 --> 01:04:37.822
I'm alive at last!

754
01:04:38.357 --> 01:04:44.455
And I'm full of joy!

755
01:04:51.137 --> 01:04:52.900
That's all very well.
but what are we gonna do about him?

756
01:04:58.473 --> 01:04:59.735
Hello?

757
01:05:03.311 --> 01:05:04.869
Do you hear me?

758
01:05:07.982 --> 01:05:09.472
Come on.

759
01:05:10.251 --> 01:05:12.446
You great useless thing.

760
01:05:18.760 --> 01:05:20.193
Sit down.

761
01:05:40.181 --> 01:05:42.046
There. Drink it down.

762
01:05:44.152 --> 01:05:47.747
Now. we got a body
moldering away upstairs.

763
01:05:47.855 --> 01:05:50.756
Now. what do you intend
we should do about that. then?

764
01:05:50.858 --> 01:05:53.122
Later on when it's dark.

765
01:05:53.227 --> 01:05:56.526
we'll take it to some secret place
and bury it.

766
01:05:56.631 --> 01:05:59.225
Oh. yeah. Course we could do that.

767
01:06:02.403 --> 01:06:03.870
Don't suppose he's got any relatives

768
01:06:03.971 --> 01:06:05.836
that's gonna come poking around
looking for him.

769
01:06:11.212 --> 01:06:13.942
Seems a downright shame

770
01:06:14.282 --> 01:06:15.544
Shame?

771
01:06:17.185 --> 01:06:19.415
Seems an awful waste

772
01:06:21.522 --> 01:06:25.458
Such a nice plump frame
What's his name has

773
01:06:25.560 --> 01:06:27.892
Had. has

774
01:06:28.396 --> 01:06:31.126
Nor it can't be traced

775
01:06:32.233 --> 01:06:34.827
Business needs a lift

776
01:06:35.636 --> 01:06:38.127
Debts to be erased

777
01:06:38.973 --> 01:06:42.170
Think of it as thrift. as a gift

778
01:06:42.877 --> 01:06:44.970
If you get my drift.

779
01:06:45.613 --> 01:06:49.014
Seems an awful waste

780
01:06:51.285 --> 01:06:54.413
I mean. with the price of meat what it is

781
01:06:54.689 --> 01:06:57.783
When you get it. if you get it

782
01:06:58.359 --> 01:06:59.485
Good. you got it

783
01:06:59.594 --> 01:07:03.553
Take. for instance
Mrs. Mooney and her pie shop

784
01:07:03.664 --> 01:07:07.760
Business never better
using only pussycats and toast

785
01:07:07.869 --> 01:07:11.737
Now a pussy's good for
maybe six or seven at the most

786
01:07:11.839 --> 01:07:13.739
And I'm sure they can't
compare as far as taste

787
01:07:13.841 --> 01:07:16.401
Mrs. Lovett. what a charming notion
Eminently practical

788
01:07:16.511 --> 01:07:18.809
-And yet appropriate as always
- Well. it does seem a waste

789
01:07:18.913 --> 01:07:21.677
Mrs. Lovett. how I've lived without you
All these years I'll never know!

790
01:07:21.782 --> 01:07:22.771
Think about it

791
01:07:22.884 --> 01:07:23.908
-lots of other gentlemen'll...
-How delectable!

792
01:07:24.018 --> 01:07:25.349
-...soon be coming for a shave
-Also undetectable

793
01:07:25.453 --> 01:07:28.251
- Won't they? Think of all them pies!
-How choice! How rare!

794
01:07:28.356 --> 01:07:31.951
For what's the sound
of the world out there?

795
01:07:32.059 --> 01:07:34.994
What. Mr. Todd. what. Mr. Todd
What is that sound?

796
01:07:35.096 --> 01:07:38.623
Those crunching
noises pervading the air?

797
01:07:38.733 --> 01:07:41.634
Yes. Mr. Todd
Yes. Mr. Todd. yes. all around

798
01:07:41.736 --> 01:07:45.001
It's man devouring man. my dear

799
01:07:45.106 --> 01:07:49.634
-And who are we to deny it in here?
-And who are we to deny it in here?

800
01:07:53.014 --> 01:07:55.915
These are desperate times. Mrs. Lovett.

801
01:07:56.617 --> 01:07:59.552
And desperate measures are called for.

802
01:07:59.820 --> 01:08:03.187
Here we are. hot out of the oven.

803
01:08:04.258 --> 01:08:05.452
What is that?

804
01:08:05.560 --> 01:08:08.586
It's priest
Have a little priest

805
01:08:08.696 --> 01:08:12.097
-Is it really good?
-Sir. it's too good. at least

806
01:08:12.200 --> 01:08:15.465
Then again
they don't commit sins of the flesh

807
01:08:15.570 --> 01:08:17.435
So it's pretty fresh

808
01:08:19.106 --> 01:08:20.733
Awful lot of fat

809
01:08:20.841 --> 01:08:22.274
Only where it sat

810
01:08:22.376 --> 01:08:25.937
Haven't you got poet
or something like that?

811
01:08:26.047 --> 01:08:30.848
No. you see the trouble with poet is
how do you know it's deceased?

812
01:08:30.952 --> 01:08:32.977
Try the priest

813
01:08:41.963 --> 01:08:43.828
Lawyer's rather nice.

814
01:08:43.931 --> 01:08:45.728
If it's for a price

815
01:08:45.833 --> 01:08:50.736
Order something else. though. to follow
Since no one should swallow it twice

816
01:08:50.838 --> 01:08:52.533
Anything that's lean?

817
01:08:52.640 --> 01:08:57.509
Well. then. if you're British and loyal
You might enjoy Royal Marine

818
01:08:57.612 --> 01:08:59.341
Anyway. it's clean

819
01:08:59.447 --> 01:09:02.610
Though. of course
it tastes of wherever it's been

820
01:09:02.717 --> 01:09:06.118
Is that squire on the fire?

821
01:09:06.220 --> 01:09:09.656
Mercy no. sir. look closer
You'll notice it's grocer

822
01:09:09.757 --> 01:09:12.749
Looks thicker
More like vicar

823
01:09:12.860 --> 01:09:16.159
No. it has to be grocer
It's green

824
01:09:19.667 --> 01:09:23.398
The history of the world. my love

825
01:09:23.504 --> 01:09:26.166
Save a lot of graves
Do a lot of relatives favors

826
01:09:26.274 --> 01:09:30.233
Is those below serving those up above

827
01:09:30.344 --> 01:09:32.904
Everybody shaves
So there should be plenty of flavors

828
01:09:33.014 --> 01:09:36.142
How gratifying for once to know

829
01:09:36.250 --> 01:09:37.683
- That those above
- That those above

830
01:09:37.785 --> 01:09:41.744
-will serve those down below!
-will serve those down below!

831
01:09:48.029 --> 01:09:49.053
What is that?

832
01:09:49.163 --> 01:09:52.564
It's fop
Finest in the shop

833
01:09:52.667 --> 01:09:57.366
Or we have some shepherd's pie
peppered with actual shepherd on top

834
01:09:57.471 --> 01:09:59.234
And I've just begun

835
01:09:59.340 --> 01:10:04.243
Here's the politician. so oily
It's served with a doily. have one

836
01:10:04.345 --> 01:10:06.040
Put it on a bun

837
01:10:06.147 --> 01:10:09.548
Well. you never know if it's going to run

838
01:10:09.650 --> 01:10:12.778
Try the friar. fried. it's drier

839
01:10:12.887 --> 01:10:16.653
No. the clergy is really
Too coarse and too mealy

840
01:10:16.757 --> 01:10:19.885
Then actor
It's compacter

841
01:10:19.994 --> 01:10:22.929
But always arrives overdone

842
01:10:23.030 --> 01:10:26.397
I' ll come again
when you have judge on the menu.

843
01:10:32.807 --> 01:10:36.334
Have charity towards the world. my pet

844
01:10:36.444 --> 01:10:39.379
Yes. yes. I know. my love

845
01:10:39.480 --> 01:10:43.075
We'll take the customers
that we can get

846
01:10:43.184 --> 01:10:45.812
High-born and low. my love

847
01:10:45.920 --> 01:10:48.912
We'll not discriminate great from small

848
01:10:49.023 --> 01:10:51.116
No. we'll serve anyone

849
01:10:51.225 --> 01:10:52.749
- We'll serve anyone
-Meaning anyone

850
01:10:52.860 --> 01:10:56.990
-And to anyone at all!
-And to anyone at all!

851
01:11:16.450 --> 01:11:17.917
So. it's true.

852
01:11:18.853 --> 01:11:23.517
Sir. a gentleman knocks
before entering a lady's room.

853
01:11:23.758 --> 01:11:26.420
Indeed he does. but I see no lady.

854
01:11:29.296 --> 01:11:31.821
I told myself the sailor was lying.

855
01:11:31.932 --> 01:11:36.301
that my Johanna would never betray me.
never hurt me so.

856
01:11:36.404 --> 01:11:39.168
Sir. I will leave this place.

857
01:11:40.341 --> 01:11:43.071
I think that only appropriate

858
01:11:43.177 --> 01:11:47.375
since you no longer find
my company to your liking.

859
01:11:49.917 --> 01:11:52.852
We shall provide you with new lodgings.

860
01:11:55.689 --> 01:11:59.489
Until this moment I have spared the rod.

861
01:12:00.761 --> 01:12:04.458
But the ungrateful child
has broken my heart.

862
01:12:06.066 --> 01:12:08.000
When you've learned
to appreciate what you have.

863
01:12:08.102 --> 01:12:09.797
perhaps we shall meet again.

864
01:12:09.904 --> 01:12:11.462
Until then

865
01:12:13.007 --> 01:12:15.874
think on your sins.

866
01:12:23.083 --> 01:12:24.277
No!

867
01:12:28.389 --> 01:12:29.913
No. please!

868
01:12:33.294 --> 01:12:36.457
Johanna! Where are you taking her?
Tell me or I swear I'll...

869
01:12:36.564 --> 01:12:39.089
You'd kill me. boy? Here I stand!

870
01:12:40.935 --> 01:12:42.425
Johanna!

871
01:13:48.936 --> 01:13:53.270
I feel you

872
01:13:53.374 --> 01:13:57.208
Johanna

873
01:13:57.311 --> 01:14:01.179
I feel you

874
01:14:01.815 --> 01:14:05.410
Do they think that walls can hide you?

875
01:14:05.519 --> 01:14:09.353
Even now. I'm at your window

876
01:14:09.456 --> 01:14:13.893
I am in the dark beside you

877
01:14:13.994 --> 01:14:19.125
Buried sweetly in your yellow hair

878
01:14:19.233 --> 01:14:23.727
Johanna

879
01:14:31.745 --> 01:14:35.306
And are you beautiful and pale

880
01:14:35.416 --> 01:14:38.510
With yellow hair. like her?

881
01:14:38.619 --> 01:14:42.077
I'd want you beautiful and pale

882
01:14:42.189 --> 01:14:48.424
The way I've dreamed you were
Johanna

883
01:14:51.865 --> 01:14:58.270
And if you're beautiful
what then with yellow hair. like wheat

884
01:14:58.372 --> 01:15:01.933
I think we shall not meet again

885
01:15:02.042 --> 01:15:05.011
My little dove. my sweet Johanna

886
01:15:05.112 --> 01:15:11.449
I'll steal you. Johanna!

887
01:15:11.552 --> 01:15:13.884
Goodbye. Johanna!

888
01:15:14.922 --> 01:15:18.016
You're gone. and yet you're mine

889
01:15:18.125 --> 01:15:20.457
I'm fine. Johanna

890
01:15:20.561 --> 01:15:27.262
-I'm fine!
-Johanna

891
01:15:34.074 --> 01:15:40.445
Smoke! Smoke! Sign of the devil
Sign of the devil. City on fire!

892
01:15:40.547 --> 01:15:43.641
Witch! Witch! Smell it. sir
An evil smell

893
01:15:43.751 --> 01:15:45.446
Every night at the vespers bell

894
01:15:45.552 --> 01:15:47.179
Smoke that comes from
the mouth of hell

895
01:15:47.287 --> 01:15:50.256
City on fire!

896
01:15:50.357 --> 01:15:53.554
City on fire

897
01:15:54.361 --> 01:15:56.921
Mischief! Mischief! Mischief!

898
01:16:05.372 --> 01:16:11.834
And if I never hear your voice
My turtledove. my dear

899
01:16:11.945 --> 01:16:17.611
I still have reason to rejoice
The way ahead is clear

900
01:16:17.718 --> 01:16:21.916
Johanna

901
01:16:23.724 --> 01:16:24.713
I feel

902
01:16:24.825 --> 01:16:30.388
And in that darkness when I'm blind
With what I can't forget

903
01:16:30.497 --> 01:16:31.521
Johanna

904
01:16:31.632 --> 01:16:34.658
It's always morning in my mind

905
01:16:34.768 --> 01:16:41.037
My little lamb. my pet. Johanna

906
01:16:44.044 --> 01:16:47.207
-You stay. Johanna...
-Johanna

907
01:16:47.314 --> 01:16:50.044
... the way I've dreamed you are

908
01:16:50.551 --> 01:16:54.146
Oh. look. Johanna! A star!

909
01:16:54.254 --> 01:16:58.816
Buried sweetly in your yellow hair

910
01:16:58.926 --> 01:17:02.327
A shooting star!

911
01:17:06.233 --> 01:17:10.169
There. there. somebody. somebody
look up there. Didn't I tell you?

912
01:17:10.270 --> 01:17:14.172
Smell that air. City on fire!

913
01:17:14.274 --> 01:17:17.175
Quick. sir. run and tell
Warn them all of the witch's spell

914
01:17:17.277 --> 01:17:18.904
There it is. there it is. the unholy smell

915
01:17:19.012 --> 01:17:21.207
Tell it to the Beadle and police as well
Tell them! Tell them

916
01:17:21.315 --> 01:17:25.149
Help. fiend! City on fire!

917
01:17:25.252 --> 01:17:28.653
City on fire

918
01:17:28.756 --> 01:17:30.519
Mischief. Mischief.

919
01:17:40.367 --> 01:17:46.795
And though I'll think of you. I guess
Until the day I die

920
01:17:46.907 --> 01:17:52.607
I think I miss you less and less
As every day goes by

921
01:17:52.713 --> 01:17:59.448
-Johanna
-Johanna

922
01:17:59.553 --> 01:18:05.890
And you'd be beautiful and pale
And look too much like her

923
01:18:05.993 --> 01:18:11.693
If only angels could prevail
We'd be the way we were

924
01:18:11.799 --> 01:18:18.671
-Johanna
-I feel you. Johanna

925
01:18:18.772 --> 01:18:21.798
Wake up. Johanna

926
01:18:21.909 --> 01:18:25.003
Another bright red day

927
01:18:25.112 --> 01:18:31.813
We learn. Johanna. to say

928
01:18:33.487 --> 01:18:34.977
Goodbye

929
01:18:38.659 --> 01:18:42.220
I'll steal

930
01:18:45.299 --> 01:18:50.168
you

931
01:19:27.641 --> 01:19:31.407
Ladies and gentlemen
May I have your attention. please?

932
01:19:32.980 --> 01:19:34.971
Are your nostrils a-quiver
and tingling as well

933
01:19:35.082 --> 01:19:38.142
At that delicate
luscious ambrosial smell?

934
01:19:38.252 --> 01:19:40.345
Yes. they are. I can tell

935
01:19:40.454 --> 01:19:44.288
Well. ladies and gentlemen
That aroma enriching the breeze

936
01:19:44.391 --> 01:19:46.325
Is like nothing
compared to its succulent source

937
01:19:46.426 --> 01:19:50.089
As the gourmets among you
will tell you. of course

938
01:19:50.197 --> 01:19:55.032
Ladies and gentlemen
You can't imagine the rapture in store

939
01:19:56.069 --> 01:19:58.367
Just inside of this door!

940
01:20:02.643 --> 01:20:06.101
There you'll sample
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

941
01:20:06.213 --> 01:20:09.671
Savory and sweet pies
As you'll see

942
01:20:09.783 --> 01:20:13.241
You who eat pies
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

943
01:20:13.353 --> 01:20:16.845
Conjure up the treat
pies used to be!

944
01:20:20.594 --> 01:20:22.323
- Toby!
-Coming!

945
01:20:23.397 --> 01:20:25.126
-Ale there!
-Right. ma'am!

946
01:20:25.232 --> 01:20:26.631
Quick. now!

947
01:20:27.868 --> 01:20:31.497
Nice to see you. dearie
How have you been keeping?

948
01:20:31.605 --> 01:20:35.200
Cor. me bones is weary
Toby! One for the gentleman

949
01:20:35.309 --> 01:20:38.870
Hear the birdies cheeping
Helps to keep it cheery

950
01:20:38.979 --> 01:20:42.415
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

951
01:20:42.516 --> 01:20:46.316
What's my secret?
Frankly. dear. forgive my candor

952
01:20:46.420 --> 01:20:49.878
Family secret
All to do with herbs

953
01:20:49.990 --> 01:20:53.448
Things like being
careful with your coriander

954
01:20:53.560 --> 01:20:55.996
That's what makes the gravy grander!

955
01:20:55.996 --> 01:20:56.291
That's what makes the gravy grander!

956
01:21:06.139 --> 01:21:09.666
Eat them slow and feel the crust
How thin she rolled it

957
01:21:09.776 --> 01:21:13.405
Eat them slow
'cause every one's a prize!

958
01:21:13.513 --> 01:21:16.949
Eat them slow 'cause that's the lot
and now we've sold it!

959
01:21:17.050 --> 01:21:18.312
Come again tomorrow!

960
01:21:18.418 --> 01:21:19.715
Hold it!

961
01:21:20.721 --> 01:21:22.780
Bless my eyes!

962
01:21:24.424 --> 01:21:26.358
Fresh supplies!

963
01:21:26.460 --> 01:21:27.825
-How about it. dearie?
-Is that a pie...

964
01:21:27.928 --> 01:21:29.725
-Be here in a twinkling!
-...fit for a king

965
01:21:29.830 --> 01:21:32.458
-Just confirms me theory. Toby!
-A wondrous sweet

966
01:21:32.566 --> 01:21:33.726
-and most delectable thing?
-God watches over us

967
01:21:33.834 --> 01:21:35.529
Didn't have an inkling. positively eerie

968
01:21:35.635 --> 01:21:36.932
You see. ma'am
why there's no meat pie

969
01:21:37.037 --> 01:21:39.699
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

970
01:21:47.781 --> 01:21:51.046
Still got to keep an eye
on the household expenditure.

971
01:21:52.686 --> 01:21:55.314
Which isn't to say we couldn't get
some nice taxidermy animals.

972
01:21:55.422 --> 01:21:57.720
bring a touch of gentility to the place.

973
01:21:57.824 --> 01:22:00.315
You know. a boar's head or two?

974
01:22:01.528 --> 01:22:05.294
-Mr. T? You listening to me?
-Of course.

975
01:22:05.899 --> 01:22:10.962
-Then what did I just say?
-There must be a way to the Judge.

976
01:22:11.071 --> 01:22:14.199
Judge. Always harping
on the bloody old judge.

977
01:22:15.242 --> 01:22:17.472
We got a nice
respectable business now.

978
01:22:17.577 --> 01:22:19.442
Money coming in regular-like.

979
01:22:19.546 --> 01:22:21.241
And since we're careful
to pick and choose.

980
01:22:21.348 --> 01:22:25.512
strangers. people who won't be missed.
who's gonna catch on?

981
01:22:27.154 --> 01:22:29.281
Mr. Todd. I'm so happy

982
01:22:29.389 --> 01:22:31.516
I could eat you up. I really could

983
01:22:31.625 --> 01:22:34.856
You know what I'd like to do. Mr. Todd?
What I dream?

984
01:22:34.961 --> 01:22:38.658
If the business stays as good
Where I'd really like to go

985
01:22:39.266 --> 01:22:43.600
In a year or so?
Don't you want to know?

986
01:22:43.703 --> 01:22:44.829
Of course.

987
01:22:44.938 --> 01:22:46.769
Do you really want to know?

988
01:22:46.873 --> 01:22:48.773
Yes. I do.

989
01:23:03.523 --> 01:23:06.492
By the sea. Mr. Todd
That's the life I'll covet

990
01:23:06.593 --> 01:23:09.460
By the sea. Mr. Todd
Oh. I know you'd love it

991
01:23:09.563 --> 01:23:14.591
You and me. Mr. T. we could be alone
In a house what we'd almost own

992
01:23:14.701 --> 01:23:17.932
-Down by the sea
-Anything you say

993
01:23:18.038 --> 01:23:20.836
Wouldn't that be smashing?

994
01:23:21.741 --> 01:23:24.869
Think how snug it'll be
Underneath our flannel

995
01:23:24.978 --> 01:23:27.947
When it's just you and me
And the English Channel

996
01:23:28.048 --> 01:23:30.846
In our cozy retreat
Kept all neat and tidy

997
01:23:30.951 --> 01:23:36.116
We'll have chums over every Friday
By the sea

998
01:23:36.223 --> 01:23:41.718
Don't you love the weather
by the sea?

999
01:23:42.596 --> 01:23:45.690
We'll grow old together

1000
01:23:45.999 --> 01:23:50.459
By the seaside
By the beautiful sea

1001
01:23:55.575 --> 01:23:58.567
It'll be so quiet that who'll come by it

1002
01:23:58.678 --> 01:24:01.010
except a seagull?

1003
01:24:01.882 --> 01:24:06.319
We shouldn't try it
though. till it's legal for two!

1004
01:24:07.687 --> 01:24:10.815
But a seaside wedding could be devised

1005
01:24:10.924 --> 01:24:13.757
Me rumpled bedding legitimized

1006
01:24:13.860 --> 01:24:19.492
Me eyelids'll flutter. I'll turn into butter
The moment I mutter "I do!"

1007
01:24:19.599 --> 01:24:23.262
Will you take this woman
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

1008
01:24:27.407 --> 01:24:29.432
You may kiss your bride.

1009
01:24:41.821 --> 01:24:47.691
Down by the sea
Married nice and proper

1010
01:24:47.894 --> 01:24:53.491
By the sea
Bring along your chopper

1011
01:24:53.600 --> 01:25:00.062
To the seaside
By the beautiful sea

1012
01:25:18.291 --> 01:25:20.919
I brought you some breakfast. dear.

1013
01:25:24.798 --> 01:25:27.824
Mr. T? Can I ask you a question?

1014
01:25:29.035 --> 01:25:30.127
What?

1015
01:25:31.204 --> 01:25:33.502
What did your Lucy look like?

1016
01:25:36.443 --> 01:25:38.707
Can't really remember. can you?

1017
01:25:40.046 --> 01:25:42.014
She had yellow hair.

1018
01:25:43.950 --> 01:25:46.851
You gotta leave this all behind.
you know.

1019
01:25:48.655 --> 01:25:50.247
She's gone.

1020
01:25:51.891 --> 01:25:54.189
Life is for the alive. my dear.

1021
01:25:55.328 --> 01:25:58.058
We could have a life. us two.

1022
01:25:58.164 --> 01:26:00.189
Maybe not like I dreamed.

1023
01:26:01.268 --> 01:26:03.429
Maybe not like you remember.

1024
01:26:04.504 --> 01:26:06.301
But we could get by.

1025
01:26:14.914 --> 01:26:19.044
-Mr. Todd! Mrs. Lovett. ma'am?
-What is it. Anthony?

1026
01:26:19.152 --> 01:26:23.020
-He has her locked in a madhouse.
-Johanna.

1027
01:26:23.123 --> 01:26:24.590
Fogg's Asylum.

1028
01:26:24.691 --> 01:26:29.458
I've circled the place a dozen times.
There's no way in. It's a fortress.

1029
01:26:29.562 --> 01:26:32.463
-I've got him.
-Mr. Todd?

1030
01:26:33.733 --> 01:26:35.360
We've got her.

1031
01:26:36.703 --> 01:26:38.068
Where do you suppose
all the wigmakers

1032
01:26:38.171 --> 01:26:40.605
in London go to obtain their hair?

1033
01:26:41.408 --> 01:26:42.636
Bedlam.

1034
01:26:43.443 --> 01:26:47.311
-They get it from the lunatics at Bedlam.
-I don't understand.

1035
01:26:48.815 --> 01:26:51.841
We shall set you up
as a wigmaker's apprentice.

1036
01:26:51.951 --> 01:26:55.079
That'll gain you access.
And then you take her.

1037
01:26:55.822 --> 01:26:57.483
Go. quickly. go!

1038
01:26:58.992 --> 01:27:00.425
Fetch the boy.

1039
01:27:00.527 --> 01:27:03.860
Don't you think you should
leave the boy behind?

1040
01:27:18.411 --> 01:27:22.507
-Toby. Mr. Todd needs you.
-Yes. ma'am.

1041
01:27:35.495 --> 01:27:36.826
Mr. T?

1042
01:27:39.399 --> 01:27:43.358
-Do you know where the Old Bailey is?
-Yes. sir. Not that I ever been there.

1043
01:27:43.470 --> 01:27:47.566
Take this there.
Seek out a Judge Turpin. Repeat that.

1044
01:27:47.674 --> 01:27:50.142
Go to Old Bailey. Find Judge Turpin.

1045
01:27:50.243 --> 01:27:53.679
You put that into his hands.
Only to him. you understand?

1046
01:27:53.780 --> 01:27:54.872
Yes. sir.

1047
01:27:54.981 --> 01:27:57.245
And while I'm out. do you mind
if I stop by the grocer just to pick...

1048
01:27:57.350 --> 01:28:00.012
No. You're not to stop.
you're not to speak.

1049
01:28:00.120 --> 01:28:02.714
You're to deliver the letter.
Do you understand?

1050
01:28:02.822 --> 01:28:04.346
Yes. sir.

1051
01:28:34.521 --> 01:28:35.988
Where you been. lad?

1052
01:28:36.089 --> 01:28:40.753
We had quite the rush at dinner time.
Me poor bones is ready to drop.

1053
01:28:40.860 --> 01:28:43.158
Mr. Todd sent me on an errand.

1054
01:28:43.263 --> 01:28:44.252
And on the way back.

1055
01:28:44.364 --> 01:28:47.231
I went by the workhouse.
just to take a look.

1056
01:28:47.333 --> 01:28:51.133
And I was thinking. but for you.
I'd be there now.

1057
01:28:52.238 --> 01:28:54.035
Or someplace worse.

1058
01:28:54.140 --> 01:28:56.131
Seems like the good Lord
sent you for me.

1059
01:28:56.242 --> 01:28:59.609
Oh. love. I feel quite the same way.

1060
01:28:59.712 --> 01:29:01.612
Listen to me. please.

1061
01:29:01.714 --> 01:29:03.978
You know there's nothing
I wouldn't do for you.

1062
01:29:04.083 --> 01:29:07.211
Say. if there were someone around.

1063
01:29:08.121 --> 01:29:09.884
someone bad?

1064
01:29:10.490 --> 01:29:12.890
Only you didn't know it.

1065
01:29:12.992 --> 01:29:16.723
What is this?
What are you talking about?

1066
01:29:18.865 --> 01:29:25.327
Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around

1067
01:29:26.806 --> 01:29:32.301
Nothing's gonna harm you
No. sir. not while I'm around

1068
01:29:32.412 --> 01:29:33.936
What do you mean "someone bad"?

1069
01:29:34.047 --> 01:29:40.577
Demons are prowling everywhere
nowadays

1070
01:29:41.421 --> 01:29:47.690
I'll send them howling. I don't care
I got ways

1071
01:29:48.962 --> 01:29:51.897
Hush. darling. there's no need for this.

1072
01:29:53.633 --> 01:30:00.004
No one's gonna hurt you
No one's gonna dare

1073
01:30:01.274 --> 01:30:06.906
Others can desert you
Not to worry. whistle. I'll be there

1074
01:30:07.747 --> 01:30:11.513
Demons will charm you
With a smile

1075
01:30:11.618 --> 01:30:17.420
For a while. but in time

1076
01:30:17.524 --> 01:30:20.288
Nothing can harm you

1077
01:30:21.528 --> 01:30:26.659
Not while I'm around

1078
01:30:30.270 --> 01:30:31.931
That's nice. dear.

1079
01:30:32.639 --> 01:30:37.269
Now. what is all this foolishness?
What are you talking about?

1080
01:30:38.011 --> 01:30:41.879
Little things that
I've been thinking about Mr. Todd.

1081
01:30:42.849 --> 01:30:47.843
Not to worry. not to worry
I may not be smart. but I ain't dumb

1082
01:30:49.122 --> 01:30:54.321
I can do it. put me to it
Show me something I can overcome

1083
01:30:55.595 --> 01:30:59.622
Not to worry. ma'am

1084
01:31:02.435 --> 01:31:06.929
Being close and being clever
Ain't like being true

1085
01:31:08.007 --> 01:31:13.536
I don't need to. I won't never
Hide a thing from you

1086
01:31:13.646 --> 01:31:17.047
Like some

1087
01:31:18.818 --> 01:31:23.016
Now. Toby. dear. haven't we
had enough of this foolish chatter?

1088
01:31:23.122 --> 01:31:24.453
Here.

1089
01:31:24.557 --> 01:31:29.722
How about I give you
a nice shiny new penny

1090
01:31:29.829 --> 01:31:32.559
and you go get us some toffees?

1091
01:31:34.901 --> 01:31:36.562
That's Signor Pirelli's purse!

1092
01:31:36.669 --> 01:31:39.502
No. it's not. Just something Mr. T
gave me for my birthday.

1093
01:31:39.606 --> 01:31:41.506
That proves it! We gotta go. ma'am.

1094
01:31:41.608 --> 01:31:43.735
We gotta find the Beadle
and get the law here!

1095
01:31:43.876 --> 01:31:46.709
Toby. Hush. lad.
you're not going anywhere.

1096
01:31:46.813 --> 01:31:51.807
You just sit here. nice and quiet.
next to me. That's right. right.

1097
01:31:54.721 --> 01:31:57.383
How could you think
such a thing of Mr. Todd?

1098
01:31:57.490 --> 01:32:00.015
He's been so good to us.

1099
01:32:04.230 --> 01:32:10.760
Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around

1100
01:32:12.572 --> 01:32:18.067
Nothing's gonna harm you. darling
Not while I'm around

1101
01:32:19.345 --> 01:32:25.011
Demons'll charm you with a smile
For a while

1102
01:32:25.118 --> 01:32:28.246
But in time

1103
01:32:28.354 --> 01:32:32.347
Nothing's gonna harm you

1104
01:32:32.458 --> 01:32:38.090
Not while I'm around

1105
01:32:41.868 --> 01:32:44.837
Funny we should be having
this little chat right now.

1106
01:32:44.937 --> 01:32:47.132
'Cause I was just thinking...

1107
01:32:48.041 --> 01:32:50.669
You know how you've always fancied
coming into the bake house with me

1108
01:32:50.777 --> 01:32:53.905
-to help make the pies?
-Yes. ma'am.

1109
01:32:54.080 --> 01:32:58.414
Well. no time like the present. eh?

1110
01:33:18.304 --> 01:33:21.740
I feel bad for you. going up
and down all these stairs.

1111
01:33:21.841 --> 01:33:25.641
-Well. that'll be your job now.
-Yes. ma'am.

1112
01:33:30.083 --> 01:33:32.347
Quite a stink. ain't there?

1113
01:33:36.055 --> 01:33:37.386
You see those grates?

1114
01:33:37.490 --> 01:33:40.288
They go right down to the sewers.
and the smells come up.

1115
01:33:40.393 --> 01:33:42.793
Always a few rats gone home
to Jesus down there.

1116
01:33:42.895 --> 01:33:46.797
Now. this'll be the bake oven.
Three dozen at a time.

1117
01:33:46.899 --> 01:33:49.663
Always be sure
the door is closed properly. like this.

1118
01:33:49.769 --> 01:33:53.364
-Door's closed properly.
-This is a grinder.

1119
01:33:53.973 --> 01:33:57.306
Pop in the meat. Give it a good grind.

1120
01:34:00.613 --> 01:34:02.308
Pops out there.

1121
01:34:04.217 --> 01:34:05.582
You try.

1122
01:34:07.286 --> 01:34:08.514
Good grind.

1123
01:34:10.156 --> 01:34:11.885
Comes out there.

1124
01:34:13.893 --> 01:34:15.224
That's my boy.

1125
01:34:15.328 --> 01:34:18.161
I'm just gonna pop upstairs.
back in two shakes. all right?

1126
01:34:18.264 --> 01:34:21.495
You mind if I have a pie while I wait?

1127
01:34:21.601 --> 01:34:23.592
As many as you like. son.

1128
01:34:36.415 --> 01:34:37.780
Yes. sir. I agree.

1129
01:34:37.884 --> 01:34:39.351
It would be to our mutual interest

1130
01:34:39.452 --> 01:34:43.388
to come to some arrangement
in regard to my poor children's hair.

1131
01:34:43.489 --> 01:34:44.922
Brunettes.

1132
01:34:46.492 --> 01:34:47.982
Redheads.

1133
01:34:50.696 --> 01:34:53.164
I keep the blondes in here.

1134
01:34:53.266 --> 01:34:55.826
It was yellow hair
you was looking for. sir?

1135
01:34:55.935 --> 01:34:57.300
Yes.

1136
01:35:28.367 --> 01:35:32.394
-That one there has the shade I need.
-Come. child.

1137
01:35:39.145 --> 01:35:42.637
Smile for the gentleman
and you shall have a sweetie.

1138
01:35:44.650 --> 01:35:46.914
Now. where shall I cut?

1139
01:35:48.321 --> 01:35:51.688
Not another word. Mr. Fogg.
or it will be your last.

1140
01:35:53.626 --> 01:35:58.495
Now. I leave you
to the mercy of your children.

1141
01:36:08.908 --> 01:36:12.241
I got him locked in.
But if he escapes. he'll go to the law.

1142
01:36:12.345 --> 01:36:14.575
-Then he won't escape.
-I don't know. Mr. Todd.

1143
01:36:14.680 --> 01:36:16.944
The Judge'll be here soon.

1144
01:36:18.517 --> 01:36:21.350
'Scuse me. sir. Gave me a fright.

1145
01:36:21.454 --> 01:36:24.446
Not my intention. good madam.
I assure you.

1146
01:36:25.224 --> 01:36:28.216
Though I am here on official business.

1147
01:36:28.895 --> 01:36:34.162
You see. there's been some complaints
about the stink from your chimney.

1148
01:36:34.267 --> 01:36:37.293
They say at night
it is something most foul.

1149
01:36:38.170 --> 01:36:41.264
Health regulations
and the general public welfare

1150
01:36:41.374 --> 01:36:43.274
naturally being my duty.

1151
01:36:43.376 --> 01:36:46.504
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to take a look

1152
01:36:49.382 --> 01:36:51.077
at your bakehouse.

1153
01:36:52.485 --> 01:36:53.975
Of course. sir.

1154
01:36:54.086 --> 01:36:57.749
But first. why don't you come upstairs?
Let me pamper you.

1155
01:36:59.525 --> 01:37:02.460
Much as I do appreciate
tonsorial doormen

1156
01:37:02.561 --> 01:37:05.029
I really ought to see
to my official obligations first.

1157
01:37:05.131 --> 01:37:07.122
I completely understand.

1158
01:37:10.503 --> 01:37:15.065
If you'll indulge me. sir.
what is that exotic aroma?

1159
01:37:18.044 --> 01:37:21.070
Me secret. is a touch of ambergris.

1160
01:37:22.448 --> 01:37:25.110
Dare I offer you something
a tad more appropriate

1161
01:37:25.217 --> 01:37:27.617
for a gentleman of your standing?

1162
01:37:27.720 --> 01:37:30.655
The ladies will greatly appreciate it. sir.

1163
01:37:33.526 --> 01:37:36.791
You're the expert in these matters.

1164
01:37:36.896 --> 01:37:38.830
Only take a moment.

1165
01:37:42.969 --> 01:37:45.460
Would you like a bit of bay rum. sir?

1166
01:37:45.571 --> 01:37:47.835
Bay rum is very bracing.

1167
01:38:53.672 --> 01:38:57.301
Let me out! Please. let me out!

1168
01:39:00.079 --> 01:39:01.706
Let me out!

1169
01:39:19.365 --> 01:39:20.525
Toby?

1170
01:39:22.334 --> 01:39:23.892
Where is he?

1171
01:39:28.007 --> 01:39:32.876
Toby. where are you. love?

1172
01:39:34.980 --> 01:39:36.242
Toby?

1173
01:39:40.219 --> 01:39:43.848
Nothing's gonna harm you

1174
01:39:43.956 --> 01:39:47.187
Not while I'm around

1175
01:39:47.293 --> 01:39:48.555
Toby?

1176
01:39:50.396 --> 01:39:52.660
Where are you hiding?

1177
01:39:54.200 --> 01:39:55.360
Toby?

1178
01:39:56.569 --> 01:39:59.766
Nothing's gonna harm you. darling

1179
01:40:02.274 --> 01:40:04.868
Not while I'm around

1180
01:40:08.914 --> 01:40:10.176
Toby?

1181
01:40:12.318 --> 01:40:13.751
Mr. Todd!

1182
01:40:15.788 --> 01:40:17.380
You wait for him here.

1183
01:40:17.490 --> 01:40:20.982
I'll return with a coach
in less than half an hour.

1184
01:40:21.093 --> 01:40:25.553
Don't worry. No one'll recognize you.
You're safe now.

1185
01:40:26.565 --> 01:40:31.400
Safe? So. we run away
and then all our dreams come true?

1186
01:40:32.505 --> 01:40:34.166
I hope so.

1187
01:40:34.974 --> 01:40:38.171
I've never had dreams. Only nightmares.

1188
01:40:39.178 --> 01:40:40.577
Johanna.

1189
01:40:41.313 --> 01:40:44.771
when we're free of this place
all the ghosts will go away.

1190
01:40:44.884 --> 01:40:48.320
No. Anthony. They never go away.

1191
01:40:49.388 --> 01:40:53.119
I'll be right back to you.
Half an hour and we'll be free.

1192
01:41:28.561 --> 01:41:31.189
Beadle! Beadle!

1193
01:41:32.398 --> 01:41:37.165
No good hiding. I saw you

1194
01:41:37.269 --> 01:41:42.229
Are you in there still. Beadle?
Beadle?

1195
01:41:42.341 --> 01:41:45.139
Beadle. dear Beadle?

1196
01:41:47.279 --> 01:41:50.407
Beadle deedle deedle
deedle deedle dumpling

1197
01:41:50.516 --> 01:41:52.711
Beadle dumpling...

1198
01:41:59.725 --> 01:42:02.751
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

1199
01:42:04.997 --> 01:42:06.487
Evil is here. sir.

1200
01:42:06.599 --> 01:42:11.195
The stink of evil. from below. from her!
Oh. she's the Devil's wife.

1201
01:42:11.303 --> 01:42:15.296
Beware her. sir.
She with no pity in her heart.

1202
01:42:17.309 --> 01:42:20.176
Don't I know you. mister?

1203
01:42:20.279 --> 01:42:21.746
Mr. Todd?

1204
01:42:33.192 --> 01:42:34.716
Where is she?

1205
01:42:36.161 --> 01:42:38.755
Below. Your Honor. With my neighbor.

1206
01:42:39.765 --> 01:42:43.326
Thank heavens
the sailor did not molest her.

1207
01:42:43.435 --> 01:42:47.997
Thank heavens. too.
she has seen the error of her ways.

1208
01:42:48.874 --> 01:42:51.138
-She has?
-Oh. yes.

1209
01:42:52.011 --> 01:42:54.309
Your lesson was well-learned.

1210
01:42:54.413 --> 01:42:58.509
She speaks only of you.
Longing for forgiveness.

1211
01:43:00.319 --> 01:43:02.480
Then she shall have it.

1212
01:43:03.555 --> 01:43:06.922
-She'll be here soon. you say?
-Yes.

1213
01:43:07.526 --> 01:43:09.494
Excellent. my friend.

1214
01:43:11.497 --> 01:43:13.158
How about a shave?

1215
01:43:14.566 --> 01:43:16.500
Sit. sir. Sit.

1216
01:43:19.505 --> 01:43:25.535
-Oh. pretty women
-Pretty women. yes

1217
01:43:25.644 --> 01:43:28.704
Johanna. Johanna

1218
01:43:28.814 --> 01:43:32.409
Pretty women
Pretty women are a wonder

1219
01:43:32.518 --> 01:43:34.110
Pretty women!

1220
01:43:34.219 --> 01:43:37.120
What we do for pretty women!

1221
01:43:37.222 --> 01:43:40.885
-Blowing out their candles
-Blowing out their candles

1222
01:43:40.993 --> 01:43:44.588
-Or combing out their hair
-Or combing out their hair

1223
01:43:44.697 --> 01:43:46.392
Then they leave

1224
01:43:46.498 --> 01:43:50.059
-Even when they leave
-Even when they leave you and vanish

1225
01:43:50.169 --> 01:43:53.070
- They still are there
- They somehow can still remain

1226
01:43:53.172 --> 01:43:58.109
- There with you. there
- They're there

1227
01:43:58.911 --> 01:44:02.506
How seldom it is
one meets a fellow spirit.

1228
01:44:02.614 --> 01:44:06.852
With fellow tastes in women. at least.

1229
01:44:06.852 --> 01:44:06.908
With fellow tastes in women. at least.

1230
01:44:07.686 --> 01:44:09.153
What's that?

1231
01:44:10.055 --> 01:44:12.956
The years. no doubt.
have changed me. sir.

1232
01:44:13.058 --> 01:44:15.959
But then. I suppose the face of a barber.

1233
01:44:16.061 --> 01:44:20.122
the face of a prisoner.
a dog. is not particularly memorable.

1234
01:44:26.872 --> 01:44:29.306
Benjamin Barker.

1235
01:44:29.641 --> 01:44:32.474
Benjamin Barker!

1236
01:45:10.315 --> 01:45:13.773
Rest now. my friend

1237
01:45:15.921 --> 01:45:20.153
Rest now forever

1238
01:45:21.627 --> 01:45:26.894
Sleep now the untroubled

1239
01:45:26.999 --> 01:45:32.562
Sleep of the angels

1240
01:45:43.749 --> 01:45:45.842
Come for a shave. have you. lad?

1241
01:45:45.951 --> 01:45:47.543
No. I...

1242
01:45:51.423 --> 01:45:54.187
Everyone needs a good shave.

1243
01:46:01.400 --> 01:46:03.459
Forget my face.

1244
01:46:07.306 --> 01:46:10.537
Die! God in heaven. die!

1245
01:46:24.389 --> 01:46:25.879
You.

1246
01:46:34.833 --> 01:46:36.630
Why did you scream?

1247
01:46:36.735 --> 01:46:39.704
He was clutching onto me dress.
but he's finished now.

1248
01:46:39.805 --> 01:46:42.239
I'll take care of it. Open the door.

1249
01:46:42.341 --> 01:46:44.639
Open the door. I said.

1250
01:47:38.830 --> 01:47:41.492
"Don't I know you?" she said.

1251
01:47:51.243 --> 01:47:53.074
You knew she lived.

1252
01:47:55.047 --> 01:47:57.311
I was only thinking of you.

1253
01:48:00.919 --> 01:48:02.887
You lied to me.

1254
01:48:02.988 --> 01:48:06.549
No. no. not lied at all
No. I never lied

1255
01:48:06.658 --> 01:48:08.319
-Lucy...
-Said she took a poison

1256
01:48:08.427 --> 01:48:10.327
she did. never said that she died

1257
01:48:10.429 --> 01:48:12.624
